---
description:
Dependency injection standards.

alwaysApply: true
---

# Dependency Injection

Use Riverpod dependency injection.

Do not introduce:

get_it

injectable

service locator

unless explicitly approved.

---

# Philosophy

Dependencies should be:

Explicit

Composable

Replaceable

Testable

---

# Ownership

Features own their dependencies.

Global dependencies are limited to:

API Client

Authentication

Secure Storage

Theme

Configuration

Analytics

---

# Provider Graph

Dependencies should flow:

Config

↓

Client

↓

Datasource

↓

Repository

↓

Controller

↓

UI

Never reverse this flow.

---

# Construction

Prefer constructor injection.

Avoid hidden dependencies.

---

# Singletons

Only create singletons for:

Dio

Hive

Secure Storage

Analytics

Everything else should remain scoped.

---

# Testing

Override providers during testing.

Avoid global mutable state.

---

# Feature Isolation

A feature should not directly instantiate another feature's repository.

Communicate through interfaces.

---

# Lazy Initialization

Initialize expensive services lazily.

Avoid unnecessary startup cost.

---

# Lifecycle

Dispose resources correctly.

Examples:

Streams

Controllers

Subscriptions

Timers

---

# Cursor Instructions

Generate dependencies using Riverpod providers.

Avoid manual singleton management.

Prefer constructor injection.

Every dependency should be easily replaceable during testing.